THE Geita Regional Police Force is looking for an unidentified woman, who is suspected of kidnapping a three-months-old baby name withheld. Geita Regional Police Commander, Senior Assistant Commissioner of Police (ACP) Henry Mwaibambe confirmed the incident over the weekend while speaking to reporters. Commander Mwaibambe said the incident took place on June 2nd this year around 5pm at CCM-Katoro Street of ​​Butundwe sub-division in Geita District in the region. “The mother of a child named Daynes Jumanne (29), a resident of Katoro town centre reported the abduction of her child to Katoro Police Station soon after the incident. It is reported that this act was committed by a woman who is still unknown up to date. “The reporter said, the kidnapper initially deceived a 12-year old girl, name withheld, who was carrying the baby. "Unidentified woman came and asked her to hold the child, so that the girl could go into a tailor’s room. It is when she got a chance to escape with the child.” Commander Mwaibambe said so far, the police force has arrested a man known as Alex Mtasima (37), a resident of Mtakuja Street at Katoro city Centre for allegedly dating the suspect. The commander urged mothers and parents to protect their children, to prevent such incidents.